The assignment da->ready_for_hashing = false; is compiled only in _DEBUG builds and is immediately followed by mhd_assert(0). In typical configurations mhd_assert(0) is non‑returning (terminates the program), so the assignment has no observable effect — removing it would not change behaviour. Therefore this operation is dead code and Rule 2.2 is violated.
